def_cn: 可疑的;靠不住的;暧昧的
def_en: If you describe something as dubious, you mean that you do not consider it to be completely honest, safe, or reliable.

def_cn: 怀疑的;无把握的;迟疑的;拿不准的
def_en: If you are dubious about something, you are not completely sure about it and have not yet made up your mind about it.

def_cn: （荣誉、名声等）不好的,不光彩的
def_en: If you say that someone has the dubious honour or the dubious pleasure of doing something, you are indicating that what they are doing is not an honour or pleasure at all, but is, in fact, unpleasant or bad.
